text: @IlkkaVertanen totally agree. I don't think the future is in customer support bots.
Artificially intelligent personalities that can accurately reflect and represent your business are 5-10 years away.  It will happen.
Bots do not need to be artificially intelligent in order to be incredibly useful.  Simple is often better.
The bottom line is:  1) There are over 1 billion people on Facebook Messenger.  2) You need a bot to reach them.  3) You will have a bot.
Hype for bots has publicly decreased while the understanding of their potential has quietly increased.

column4: they simply need to send you a message.

text: The best chatbots won't replicate existing websites or mobile apps
column4: but instead they will augment them with experiences unique to messaging.

text: The first wave of successful chatbots will likely not utilize any machine learning or natural language processing. Advanced tech =/= better.
Chatbots will not only be used for customer support. They will be used for entertainment
column4: education

text: Messaging apps are used more than social networks. Every business needs a messaging strategy. Chatbots are the only scaleable solution.
People think chatbots are artificially intelligent people replacements. I disagree. Chatbots are lightweight apps delivered via messaging.
Chatbots are in the "fart app" stage where people try silly things to feel out the medium. The experiences will rapidly get better.
